  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2003-02-25",
    "date": "2006-11-28T17:35:40Z",
    "text": "Family Farm Tax Simplification Act of 2003 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to exempt from treatment as a partnership a qualified farming joint venture conducted by a jointly-filing husband and wife. Provides that income, gain, loss, deductions, and credits shall be equally divided, and treated as if attributable to a trade or business conducted by each spouse as a sole proprietor.Defines \"qualified farming joint venture.\"Amends the Code and the Social Security Act to treat such income as net earnings from self-employment, respectively."
  },
